items.title: Trump says he may send Tomahawk missiles to Ukraine
items.description: Ukraine wants long-range missiles to hit back at Russia - and Donald Trump says he may send Tomahawks.

items.title: Madagascar presidency says attempt to seize power under way
items.description: An army unit claimed it had taken over leadership of the military command and was now in control of all the armed forces.

items.title: China accuses US of 'double standards' over tariff threat
items.description: Beijing says it could introduce "countermeasures" if the US President imposes an an additional 100% tariff on Chinese imports.

items.title: Sikh man with tumour held by US immigration denied medical care - family
items.description: Paramjit Singh, an Indian passport holder, has lived in the US on a green card since 1994.

items.title: Trump says 'war is over' in Gaza as he flies to Israel for release of hostages
items.description: The US president tells reporters on board Air Force One the ceasefire "is going to hold".
